text: As a fan of Frankie Valli and The Four Seasons since 1962, how wonderful it is for me to add the first post. This movie trailer is just a taste of how great this movie is going to be. I have been going to the live concerts since 1968. I saw Jersey Boys on Broadway for the first time November 5, 2006. This was the last preview night. I had the pleasure of talking to Bob and Frankie that night. I said, "This show is going to be a smash hit!" Eight years later, I'll paraphrase what I said, "This movie is going to be a smash hit!" What a sweet feeling for all of the Seasons' fans who  took a lot of ridicule when the music scene changed so many times over the last 50 years. We said Frankie Valli and The Four Seasons were great, and we were right!

Great nostalgia trip for the over 50's and anyone who knows anything regarding the fantastic Frankie Valli and his crew..........I still think PACINO shoulda hadda oughta played Chip Ce Carlo though, but the guy that played Joe Pesci was a sensation.The lady who played F,V's first wife should have stayed away, far too hammy a portrayal.The music was superb, even if it was in a lower key to Frankies original..........Loved it anyway,
